Khayelitsha (File) (Shutterstock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - A Swedish tour group has been robbed in Khayelitsha, Cape Town, Western Cape police said on Wednesday."[On Monday] around 11:40 a group of 17 Swedish tourists, a tour guide, and a driver were robbed at gunpoint by four armed suspects while they visited a cr&egrave;che in Site C Khayelitsha," Lieutenant Colonel Andre Traut said.The robbers fled with various items and cash. They had not been arrested by Wednesday morning.No one was injured in the robbery.Traut would not immediately comment on a report that the armed robbers were believed to be children.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.